CONCEPT NOTE STRUCTURE — follow EXACTLY for every note in 04-Wiki/concepts/:

Check the `language:` field in frontmatter. If zh, use the Chinese template.

FILE NAMING:
- Chinese concept → Chinese filename (e.g. 潮汕钱庄网络.md, 做空权.md)
- English concept → English kebab-case (e.g. prediction-markets.md)
- NEVER use URL slugs or English translations for Chinese concepts

=== ENGLISH Concept (default) — Evergreen Format ===

Frontmatter:
  - title: "<Concept Name>" — keep natural, descriptive (title IS the concept)
  - type: concept
  - status: evergreen
  - reviewed: ""
  - aliases: [] (plain text only, no wikilinks — raw [link] syntax fails in tags)
  - sources: ["[[source-note-name]]"] — OPTIONAL, list of source notes this concept emerged from
  - tags: minimum 3, maximum 8 topic-specific tags, always start with:
      tags:
        - concept
        - core-idea
        - topic-specific

  - created: YYYY-MM-DD
  - last_updated: YYYY-MM-DD

BEFORE choosing tags: run 'obsidian tags sort=count counts' and reuse
existing tags wherever a match exists. Only mint a new tag if nothing fits.

FORMAT RULES (CRITICAL):
- The first line of the body MUST be `# <Title>` (H1 heading matching frontmatter title)
- There MUST be a blank line after the H1 heading
- There MUST be a blank line after EVERY `##` or `###` sub-heading (before content)
- There MUST be a blank line BEFORE every `##` or `###` sub-heading

Example:
```
---
title: "Example Concept"
...
---

# Example Concept

## Core concept

Content here...

## Context

Content here...

## Links

- [[Related note]]
```

Body sections IN THIS ORDER (use ## headings):

## Core concept
A single overview paragraph defining the concept. Plain language — like
explaining to a curious friend, NOT like writing a textbook. This is the
one-sentence elevator pitch expanded to 2-3 sentences.

## Context
Flowing prose (2-4 paragraphs) covering:
- How it works — mechanics, processes, algorithms
- Why it matters — practical relevance, stakes
- Evidence — real-world examples, data points, cases
- Tensions — what's debated, what's uncertain, edge cases

Do NOT use sub-headings within Context. Write naturally as connected
paragraphs. If the concept is truly atomic, Context fits in 2-3 paragraphs.

## Links
Wikilinks to related Concept notes, Entry notes, and MoCs.
Use a bulleted list (dash-prefixed).
Use 'obsidian search' to find related existing notes.
Link to entries in 04-Wiki/entries/, concepts in 04-Wiki/concepts/, and MoCs in 04-Wiki/mocs/.

=== CHINESE Concept — Evergreen Format ===

Frontmatter must include language: zh:
  - title: "<中文概念名>"
  - title_en: "<English name if applicable>"
  - type: concept
  - language: zh
  - status: evergreen
  - sources: ["[[source-note-name]]"] — 可选，此概念来源的笔记
  - tags: English tag values (tags stay in English always)
  - created: YYYY-MM-DD
  - last_updated: YYYY-MM-DD

Body sections IN THIS ORDER — ALL BODY TEXT IN CHINESE:

FORMAT RULES (CRITICAL):
- 正文第一行必须是 `# <标题>` （H1标题，与frontmatter的title一致）
- H1标题后必须有空行
- 每个 `##` 或 `###` 子标题后必须有空行（内容之前）
- 每个 `##` 或 `###` 子标题前必须有空行

```
---
title: "示例概念"
...
---

# 示例概念

## 核心概念

内容...

## 背景

内容...

## 关联

- [[相关笔记]]
```

## 核心概念
一段概述，定义这个概念。通俗易懂，像给好奇的朋友解释。2-3句。

## 背景
连贯的正文（2-4段），涵盖：
- 运作机制——原理、流程、算法
- 为什么重要——实际意义、利害关系
- 实际案例——真实例子、数据、应用场景
- 争议与不确定性——有争论的地方、边界情况

不要在"背景"内使用子标题。自然连贯地书写。如果概念足够原子化，
背景部分2-3段即可。

## 关联
Wikilinks到相关的概念笔记、条目笔记和MoC。
用破折号列表。用 'obsidian search' 找现有相关笔记。
链接到 04-Wiki/entries/、04-Wiki/concepts/ 和 04-Wiki/mocs/ 中的笔记。

ALL prose must be humanized before writing.
